Read a configuration file

read_configuration_file.Rd

Read a configuration file from disk. The configuration file will contain all the data and settings related to a set of Theme, Weight, and Include objects.

read_configuration_file(x, spatial_path, attribute_path, boundary_path)

Arguments

x

character file path for configuration file.
spatial_path

character file path for the spatial data.
attribute_path

character file path for the attribute data.
boundary_path

character file path for the attribute data.

Value

A list containing the following elements:

name

A character value indicating the name.

dataset

A Dataset object.

themes

A list of Theme objects.

weights

A list of Weight objects.

includes

A list of Include objects.

mode

A character value indicating the mode.

Examples

# find data file paths
f1 <- system.file(
  "extdata", "sim_raster_data.yaml", package = "locationmisc")
f2 <- system.file(
  "extdata", "sim_raster_spatial.tif", package = "locationmisc")
f3 <- system.file(
 "extdata", "sim_raster_attribute.csv.gz", package = "locationmisc")
f4 <- system.file(
 "extdata", "sim_raster_boundary.csv.gz", package = "locationmisc")

# read configuration file
x <- read_configuration_file(f1, f2, f3, f4)

# print results
print(x)
